# Eval AI Cost Rules

## Do NOT re-call the AI when retesting failures

When `npm run eval:ai -- --only-failures` runs, it re-tests cases that failed. **Use the cached output from failures.json** â€” do not call the AI API again. Each AI call costs money; retries should only re-run validation/visual tests with the same response.

## Implementation

- **failures.json** stores `actual` (the AI output) for each failed case
- **--only-failures** loads failures and passes `cachedOutput: f.actual` to the runner
- Runners accept optional `cachedOutput`; when provided, skip the `generate*` call and use it instead

## Active eval focus

`lib/ai/eval/page.json` currently has **one case**: `fashion-homepage-full` (Modern Fashion Ecommerce Homepage). This is the primary test case being developed. Do not add unrelated cases until this one is stable.

